title: Hayek transfers to Wayne Hills
text:
Hayek transfers to Wayne Hills October 9, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 9, 2015, 11:50 AM By Staff report MICHAEL KARAS/STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER All-North Jersey track runner Hunter Hayek, left, has transferred to Wayne Hills. 
All-North Jersey track performer and football wide receiver Hunter Hayek has transferred from St. Joseph to Wayne Hills, according to a St. Joseph official. 
Hayek was part of the Green Knights' 4-x-100 relay team -- which included twin brother, Tyler -- honored as the best in North Jersey last spring by The Record. It also was named first-team All-Bergen County. 
The relay team ran 42.48 seconds in winning the state Non-Public A title, second best all time, before taking fourth in the state Meet of Champions in 42.52. 
This fall the 5-foot-11, 175-pound junior starter had five receptions for 88 yards in five football games, according to MaxPreps, for St. Joseph (4-1), the No. 1-ranked team in The Record Non-Public Top 6. Â© 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
